  productName: Canon Camera
  productDescription: '1 - The Canon AT-1 is a 35mm film SLR camera manufactured
    by Canon in 1977 as a simplified version of the Canon AT-1.

    2 - It features
    manual exposure control, giving photographers full creative control over aperture
    and shutter speed settings.

    3 - The camera uses the Canon FD lens mount,
    making it compatible with a wide range of Canon FD and FL lenses.

    4 - It
    has a shutter speed range of 1/1000 to 2 seconds, plus Bulb mode for long exposures.

    5
    - The Canon AT-1 was designed as an entry-level camera for beginners who wanted
    to learn manual photography without advanced automation.'
