  productNameText: {fileID: 1439306505}
  productInfoText: {fileID: 2145969868}
  productName: Phone
  productDescription: '1 - This is a candlestick telephone, used in the late 19th
    and early 20th centuries.

    2 - It was developed after the invention of the
    telephone by Alexander Graham Bell in 1876.

    3 - The phone has a fixed mouthpiece
    for speaking and a separate receiver for listening.

    4 - Some versions included
    a rotary dial, while older ones required an operator to connect calls.

    5
    - It works by converting sound into electrical signals sent through wires.

    6
    - Today, it is considered a vintage device and shows the early development of
    communication technology.'
