  productNameText: {fileID: 129158087}
  productInfoText: {fileID: 2004355206}
  productName: Gramophone
  productDescription: '1 - The gramophone is one of the earliest devices used to
    record and play sound.

    2 - It was invented by Emile Berliner in the late
    19th century.

    3 - The device plays music using a rotating disc called a
    vinyl record.

    4 - Sound is produced when a needle moves through grooves
    on the record surface.

    5 - Gramophones became very popular for listening
    to music before modern audio technology appeared.

    6 - Today, gramophones
    are considered vintage devices and are often used for decoration and collecting.'
