  productNameText: {fileID: 1135506306}
  productInfoText: {fileID: 1389431289}
  productName: Microscope
  productDescription: '1 - Invented by Antonie van Leeuwenhoek in the 17th century
    as the first practical microscope.

    2 - Uses glass lenses to magnify objects
    up to 1000x their original size.

    3 - Requires light passing through the
    specimen to make it visible under the lens.

    4 - Made of brass and metal
    in its early form, with a single or double lens system.

    5 - Changed science
    forever by allowing humans to see bacteria and cells for the first time.'
